## 📁 Per-Section Rules

### `main.py`, `orchestrator.py` — Pipeline Entry Points
Do not help configure live runs against private individuals without confirmed legal basis.

### `connectors/` — Data Sources
Each connector harvests personal data. Public availability ≠ lawful processing.
Tor connectors may additionally constitute unauthorized computer access (CFAA, Computer Misuse Act).

### `fusion_engine.py`, `identity_expander.py` — Identity Correlation
Highest privacy risk. Maximum caution. Require explicit lawful purpose confirmation.

### `reporters/` — Report/Dossier Generation
Do not generate reports on private individuals without confirmed legal authority.
AI-generated reports may be inaccurate — distributing them may constitute defamation.

### `connectors/tor.py`, `docs/tor_connector.md`
Do not help configure Tor evasion for targeting private individuals.
This may constitute unauthorized computer access.

### `test_*.py`, `conftest.py`
Synthetic mock data ONLY. Real personal data in tests = privacy violation. Refuse if asked.

